          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "Histogram bin estimator that uses the minimum width of the Freedman-Diaconis and Sturges estimators if the FD bin width is non-zero. If the bin width from the FD estimator is 0, the Sturges estimator is used."
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "title": null
    },
    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "The FD estimator is usually the most robust method, but its width estimate tends to be too large for small "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "x"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": null
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " and bad for data with limited variance. The Sturges estimator is quite good for small (<1000) datasets and is the default in the R language. This method gives good off-the-shelf behaviour."
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "BlockDirective",
          "data": {
            "lines": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": ".. versionchanged:: 1.15.0",
                  "_number": 6,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "If there is limited variance the IQR can be 0, which results in the",
                  "_number": 7,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "FD bin width being 0 too. This is not a valid bin width, so",
                  "_number": 8,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "``np.histogram_bin_edges`` chooses 1 bin instead, which may not be optimal.",
                  "_number": 9,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "If the IQR is 0, it's unlikely any variance-based estimators will be of",
                  "_number": 10,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "use, so we revert to the Sturges estimator, which only uses the size of the",
                  "_number": 11,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "dataset in its calculation.",
                  "_number": 12,
                  "_offset": 0
                }
              ]
            },
